FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE IN TURKEY (THRACE REGION)
-------------------------------------------------
According to an e-mail received on 29 Jun 2001 from Dr. Huseyin Sungur,
General Director of Protection and Control, Ministry of Agriculture and
Rural Affairs, Ankara, an outbreak of foot and mouth disease (virus type
O1) has been reported in the village of Bagpinari (Malkara district,
Tekirdag province).
Date of initial detection: 17 Jun 2001
Number of animals present in the outbreak: 300 goats
Number of cases: 40
Number of deaths: 1
Origin: unknown
Control measures: ring vaccination (1831 cattle, 3923 sheep and goats in 5
villages around the outbreak), control of animal movements, strict
quarantine measures, disinfection, symptomatic treatment.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Previous outbreaks reported to OIE in 1999 and ProMED-mail this year have
involved cattle and sheep. Please note that this outbreak is in goats and
it is an O1 strain. - Mod.PC
